Hi.

My contention is that this kind of rhetoric in the media cannot be
used as a proxy for what the Cuban government is aiming at.

Evolving domestic legislation about usage of communication
technology and internet access for Cuban nationals
(i.e. including non-government related endeavours) would be a
better indicator of an authentic open up.

The government may even be inclined to break a deal
with an international MNO (China mobile?) to leapfrog internet access
thru RAN rather than promoting a blend of CWN, fiber, ADSL, etc.

Hopefully, one see any progress this year.

regards,
Claro.


