=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D  Apologies for cross-posting  =3D=3D=3D=3D=3D

At the Communications and Information Systems Group (CISG) at EEE UCL we ar=
e looking for a talented post-doctoral researcher to join our team, as part=
 of one of our H2020 EU-funded projects.

The UMOBILE project (=93Universal, mobile-centric and opportunistic communi=
cations architecture=94) aims to investigate and develop a communication an=
d information infrastructure for underserved, rural, developing regions inl=
ine with the objectives of the Global Access to the Internet for All (GAIA)=
 group of the Internet Research Task Force (IRTF). The project will also fo=
cus on smart city communication environments.

- The position is available immediately (ideal start March 2015, but earlie=
r, or slightly later start will also be considered) for one year and possib=
ility of further extension after that period.
- The deadline for applications is the 12th of January 2015. Salary is depe=
ndent on qualifications and experience.
- The post is Grade 7, starting salary =A333,353 per annum and maximum sala=
ry =A340,313 per annum, both including London Allowance which is currently =
=A32,919 per annum.


The requirements for this position are:

- PhD in Computer Science, Electrical/Computer Engineering, or a related fi=
eld.

- Strong software design/implementation and prototyping skills

- Background and/or hands-on experience in any of the following areas:
-- Content-oriented architectures
-- Information-Centric Networks
-- Opportunistic, Delay-Tolerant Networks
-- Traffic engineering, resource management and congestion control

- Algorithm design skills

- Strong publication record

The application should include:
- a short cover letter indicating the candidate's research interests, achie=
vements to date and vision for the future,
- CV including list of publications,
- contact details of two/three referees.

Interested applicants are encouraged to make informal enquiries about the p=
ost to Dr Ioannis Psaras (i.psaras@ucl.ac.uk<mailto:i.psaras@ucl.ac.uk><mai=
lto:i.psaras@ucl.ac.uk>), or Prof. George Pavlou (g.pavlou@ucl.ac.uk<mailto=
:g.pavlou@ucl.ac.uk><mailto:g.pavlou@ucl.ac.uk>). Shortlisted candidates wi=
ll be invited for an interview shortly after the application deadline. For =
details and further particulars, please see:http://www.ee.ucl.ac.uk/vacanci=
es/research/research-associate-position-in-content-oriented-opportunistic-n=
etworking<http://www.ee.ucl.ac.uk/vacancies/research/research-associate-pos=
ition-in-content-oriented-opportunistic-networking>

