Hi Marco,

A gentle reminder of Matthew Ford's plea for some context along with any
urls posted.

What is most interesting for me about Rhizomatica a the moment and which is
not covered in the article, is the fact that they have managed to get the
regulator to allocate 2x5MHz (2x2.5MHz in some cases) of mobile spectrum
(850MHz band) as primary spectrum offering the right for non-profits to
offer telecom and broadcast services that have cultural, scientific,
educational or community objectives.  This is absolutely huge news.
Primary spectrum for rural GSM initiatives.  I suspect there are VERY few
regulators in Africa that could not squeeze 10MHz out of their 900MHz band
assignments.

Here is the news story (in Spanish)
http://www.zocalo.com.mx/seccion/articulo/ifetel-determina-las-frecuencias-y-bandas-que-se-licitaran-en-2015-14192825

Propagating this as a regulatory strategy could unleash pent-up markets for
low-cost GSM startups like Range, Endaga, Fairwaves, and others.

Cheers... Steve



